---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MathTiers from '../../components/MathTiers.astro';
---
<Layout>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-5">
    <div class="pt-10 pb-4">
      <a href="/samples" class="label hover:underline">&larr; Panel samples</a>
      <div class="part-kicker mt-4">Option B</div>
      <h1 class="part-title">Margin Notes (Tufte)</h1>
      <p class="prose-manual max-w-2xl">
        The maths lives in the right margin, anchored to the sentence it explains. A marker
        in the text expands the note in place; on narrow screens it folds inline beneath the
        paragraph. Keeps maths and prose physically adjacent without leaving the page.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="py-6 border-t border-[var(--color-rule)]">
      <div class="label mb-2">Section 02</div>
      <h3 class="text-xl mb-4">The Traction Budget</h3>

      <div class="mn-grid">
        <div class="mn-text prose-manual">
          <p>
            At the limit you get <strong>one</strong> of: 100% throttle, 100% brake, or 100%
            lean. They share a single budget of grip — brake at 70% and you can still lean at
            70%, because the demands add as a vector, not a sum.<label class="mn-marker" for="mn1">&sum;</label>
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            That's the intuition. Open the margin note to see the exact relationship and how
            it bends once real tyres, load and camber enter.
          </p>
        </div>

        <input type="checkbox" id="mn1" class="mn-toggle" />
        <aside class="mn-note">
          <label for="mn1" class="mn-note-head">
            <span class="label"><span class="section-num">&sum;</span>&nbsp;The Maths</span>
            <span class="mn-chev">&#9662;</span>
          </label>
          <div class="mn-note-body">
            <MathTiers />
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    .mn-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0,1fr) 340px; gap: 2rem; align-items: start; }
    .mn-text { max-width: 38rem; }
    .mn-marker {
      display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      width: 1.1rem; height: 1.1rem; margin-left: 0.25rem; transform: translateY(-2px);
      font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; cursor: pointer;
      color: var(--color-racing); border: 1px solid var(--color-racing); border-radius: 2px;
    }
    .mn-toggle { display: none; }
    .mn-note { border: 1px solid var(--color-rule); background: var(--color-card); }
    .mn-note-head {
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
      padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem; cursor: pointer; border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    }
    .mn-note-body { padding: 0 0.9rem; max-height: 0; overflow: hidden; transition: max-height 0.3s ease; }
    .mn-toggle:checked ~ .mn-note .mn-note-head { border-bottom-color: var(--color-rule); }
    .mn-toggle:checked ~ .mn-note .mn-note-body { max-height: 2400px; padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem 1rem; }
    .mn-toggle:checked ~ .mn-note .mn-chev { transform: rotate(180deg); }
    .mn-chev { font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--color-ink-faint); transition: transform 0.2s ease; }

    @media (max-width: 820px) {
      .mn-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .mn-note { margin-top: 0.5rem; }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
